## 📞 How WebRTC Calls Work

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as User A (Caller)
    participant S as Socket.io Server
    participant B as User B (Receiver)
    
    A->>S: call:initiate (SDP offer)
    S->>B: call:incoming (SDP offer)
    B->>S: call:answer (SDP answer)
    S->>A: call:answered (SDP answer)
    A->>S: call:ice-candidate
    S->>B: call:ice-candidate
    B->>S: call:ice-candidate
    S->>A: call:ice-candidate
    Note over A,B: P2P connection established<br/>Audio/Video goes directly A↔B
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The server is a **zero-knowledge relay**. It only passes signaling data (SDP offers/answers + ICE candidates). All audio/video streams flow directly between peers.
